			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>DeFacto: Language-Parametric Fact Extraction from Source Code</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/HendrikusJSBasten.html">Hendrikus J. S. Basten</a>, <a href="../profile/PaulKlint.html">Paul Klint</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_17">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_17</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagM">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It provides language-parametric fact extraction that underpins systematic language/source-code analysis.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The contribution includes a reusable extraction/analysis infrastructure intended to be plugged into tools.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagL">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> Language-parametricity and separable annotations enable reuse of the same extractor across many languages.
</li></ul></li></ul>
